name: Prosperity Traditional Cakes
description:
A pack of the best 3 rice-based popular CNY’s treats, consisting of

Nian Gao
Nian Gao or “kue keranjang” has a sweet caramel taste and sticky texture. Eating Nian Gao is accompanied by the phrase “Getting higher year-after-year by year,” meaning a general improvement in life. 

Fa Gao
It’s a steamed rice flour cake. Fa gao translates to “prosperity cake,” so it’s no surprise that these treats are popular during the Chinese New Year.

Dou Sa Siu Beng
Red bean paste rice cake is a classic Cantonese snack or street food in Hong Kong. It’s made from glutinous rice flour and filled with red bean paste. It has a sticky texture. 

Get your packs to celebrate this beautiful new year!
